The paper deals with the geometric properties of planar graphs, specifically the edge-length ratio of planar straight-line drawings. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the structure of planar graphs, which could fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses upper bounds on the edge-length ratio for specific families of planar graphs, which could fall under algorithms and data structures (cs.SI).
